    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @tedlin182, thanks for reaching us with your use-case. \r\n\r\nYou're right when passing the `searchState` props to an `<InstantSearch />`instance, you need to provide the entire state, we don't perform any kind of merge. But if you are listening to the `onSearchStateChange` hook, you are able to retrieved the entire state. Are you using it?\r\n\r\nAlso to have a better understanding of what you are trying to achieve, maybe you can provide us a gif showing what you have today in term of behavior and some simplify code showing how you use the library? (if you can link a repo it would even be easier). \r\n\r\nI also have some questions:\r\nWhat behavior requires you to pass a `searchState` to an `<InstantSearch/>` instance? \r\nWhich part of the `react-instantsearch` library are you using to build your `All Results` component? Which widget or connector?\r\nWhen you talk about the \"Load More\" component using the `InfiniteHits` widget, I assume that you only use the \"load more\" button and hide the rest? \r\n\r\n\r\n",
