    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hey @mthuret !\r\n\r\nThanks for your help!\r\n\r\nSo I forgot I was using a custom input text field component instead of your `SearchBox` widget, so we were manually setting the `searchState.query` down thus it was overwriting it. I replaced it back with your `SearchBox` and the load more seems to work.\r\n\r\nHowever, now I have another issue where after I click show more, load the \"show more\" view and then click back to the \"all results\" view, it clears out the `SearchBox` query, triggers the `onSearchStateChange` and resets the `searchState` to `{page: 0}`.\r\n\r\nThe `ShowMoreResults` component uses `InfiniteHits` and `AllResults` uses `Hits`. The only thing I am doing to change the views is changing a state value in my parent component from `true` to `false`.\r\n\r\nHere's a high-level outline of my component structure:\r\n\r\n```\r\nSiteSearch.jsx\r\n     - AllResults.jsx\r\n     - ShowMoreResults.jsx (this is only added in when a user clicks \"show more\" in the AllResults component)\r\n     - SearchBox\r\n     - onSearchStateChange\r\n\r\nAllResults.jsx\r\n     - Category1Results.jsx\r\n     - Category2Results.jsx\r\n     - Category3Results.jsx\r\n     - Category4Results.jsx\r\n\r\nShowMoreResults.jsx\r\n     - InfiniteHits\r\n     - InstantSearch\r\n     - VirtualSearchBox (uses connectSearchBox per the example on your site)\r\n\r\nEach category results is built as follows:\r\n     - InstantSearch (w/ unique indexName)\r\n     - Hits\r\n     - VirtualSearchBox (uses connectSearchBox per the example on your site)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI pass down `searchState` and `onSearchStateChange` down to the `AllResults` and `ShowMoreResults` components.\r\n\r\n**Update:**\r\n\r\n- I added some console.log's in `transitionState` within `connectInfiniteHits` and it looks like `prevSearchState` and `nextSearchState` are both empty objects and thus equal, thus it returns a `searchState` of `{page: 0}`\r\n\r\n**Another update:**\r\n\r\n- Looks like it could be linked to the fact that I am mounting and unmounting my `ShowMoreResults` component as I change views and thus resets the `searchState`.",
