    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hey @mthuret \r\n\r\nSorry I forgot to post a gif of the behavior we want. I had to run to catch a flight, but it's below for you to view.\r\n\r\nThe `SiteSearch` component is the main wrapper component that contains both `AllResults` and `ShowMoreResults`. We toggle between the `AllResults` and `ShowMoreResults` views via a state change (`viewShowMore') in `SiteSearch`.\r\n\r\n**`AllResults.jsx`**\r\n- This contains each category's results, each having their own \"Show more\" link that brings in the `ShowMoreResults` component/view.\r\n- Each category results component have their own `<InstantSearch/>` with their own index, `<Hits/>`, and `<VirtualSearchBox/>`.\r\n- I pass in the `searchState` and `onSearchStateChange` method down from `SiteSearch` to each of these category results components.\r\n- Also using `createConnector` to hide results when not matches are found.\r\n\r\n**`ShowMoreResults.jsx`**\r\n- This contains a specific category's results that match the current query in the `<SearchBox/>`\r\n- It has its own `<InstantSearch/>` with their own index, `<InfiniteHits/>`, and `<VirtualSearchBox/>`\r\n- We limit the initial display to show 5 results and want the user to be able to load more matching results for that specific category when they click \"Load More\".\r\n- There's also a \"Back to all results\" link that just toggles the state `viewShowMore` in `SiteSearch` that unmounts the `ShowMoreResults` component/view and brings back in the `AllResults` view.\r\n- Also using `createConnector` to hide results when not matches are found.\r\n- **Note:** We don't unmount `AllResults` ever, just `ShowMoreResults`\r\n\r\nI tested out NOT unmounting `ShowMoreResults` and it seemed to resolve that issue regarding the reset `searchState` but then I ran into other issues.\r\n\r\nHere is a video of the behavior we're trying to achieve and at the very end you'll notice the results dropdown closing automatically when we hit \"Back to results\". That is the part where `query` isn't returned back in `searchState` after we unmount `ShowMoreResults`.\r\n\r\n<http://recordit.co/jMTPlwepYJ>\r\n\r\nLet me know if you want any other info but hopefully this helps.\r\n\r\nThanks!",
