    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@tedlin182 Thanks for the gif, it's definitely clearer :) \r\n\r\nSo yes, either you manage not to unmount the <ShowMoreResults/> component, or your <SitreSearch/> component should keep track of the page cursor (this way, you can control when to reset it, or not).\r\n\r\nI did have a suggestion though, that may simplify your code. Why not only use the `connectInfiniteHits`connector to achieve the same behavior. \r\n\r\n* By default, when typing a query, each category will be displayed with 5 results and a show more button. \r\n* When clicking on a show more button, you actually hide every other categories and just continue to display hits from the wanted one.\r\n\r\nDo you think this could work for you? ",
