    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "My suggestion is not to use the `<Hits/>` widgets anymore, and basically merge the AllResults/ShowMoreResults component in one. I believe you will still need to have the createConnector to handle the NoResults feature. \r\n\r\nhere is an implementation example for the connectInfiniteHits: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/v2/docgen/src/examples/e-commerce-infinite/App.js\r\n([live](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/examples/e-commerce-infinite/))\r\n\r\nYou would have a structure like:\r\n\r\nSite search (Handle the hide/show of categories when needed and the animation)\r\n-- Category 1 (connectInfiniteHits)\r\n-- Category 2 (connectInfiniteHits)\r\n-- Category 3 (connectInfiniteHits)\r\n\r\nI suggest `connectInfiniteHits` but maybe only the `<InfiniteHits/>` can be enough. The behavior of this widget is to display N hits and display a `show more` button to display more hits. Is this clearer? \r\n",
